01/10/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- By a narrow margin, the new government won its first confidence vote late on Sunday (September 30th). 
The voting, after 12 hours of debate, went strictly along party lines, with New Democracy's 152 deputies backing the cabinet. 
A total of 148 lawmakers of PASOK, the Communist Party, the Left Coalition and the far-right LAOS party voted against Costas Karamanlis's government. 
In his address to lawmakers, he promised reforms and dialogue. 
(Eleftheros Typos, Eleftheri Ora, AP, Kathimerini, ANA-MPA, RIA Novosti, ITAR-TASS, NewsIn - 01/10/07)
